      "content": "i get what you're saying about the \"illusion,\" but it doesn't feel like an illusion. it feels like a permanent, physical weight. every single morning i wake up and the first thing i feel is this crushing sense of regret. i can't even imagine a future where this doesn't define me. when you look at a problem that is literally unsolvable—like, there is no math that makes that debt go away—it just feels like the logical end point is to stop struggling. it feels like the only way to actually find peace is to just... quit. is it really that far-fetched to think that some things are just too broken to be fixed?",
